2020 Fall Planning Survey

As the Minnesota Department of Education works closely with the Minnesota Department of Health to plan for the 2020-21 school year, we want to hear from families about their experience with the distance learning this spring.

This feedback is extremely valuable to us. This information will allow us to help families as they balance the responsibilities of work and family, while also supporting student learning.

post_text: Summer Meals Information from Food & Nutrition
shared_text:
Willmar Public Schools Food and Nutrition Services
June 1 at 9:18 AM ·

Hello everyone,

We are excited to share that we will be providing free meals for students under the age of 18 from June 4th-August 21st (no meal service on July 3rd). We will continue to provide a cold packed breakfast and lunch meal to students.

Due to limited funding for busing, we have changed our bus routes and limited where we will be going to deliver meals. If you have children under the age of 18 years of age and do not live in an area where a bus stops, you are welcome to come to any bus stop or to Lakeland Elementary or Willmar Senior High to pick up meals starting June 4th.

Update bus routes for June 4-August 21st are in new photo albums: 1 for Willmar Bus Company and 1 for Palmer Bus Company.

*Please note that there has been a change for our buses and they are now required to have their 8-ways on and their stop signs out. Please make sure to stop for buses if you see them on the street with their lights on*

Please let us know if you have any questions.
Willmar Public School District
Kandiyohi County Food Shelf

We’ve recently partnered with a company called Teachers On Call to assist with our substitute teacher and substitute paraprofessional staffing process. TOC specializes in educational staffing, and we’re confident they’ll help to make the process seamless for everyone. Teachers On Call also offers some awesome benefits that we think you’ll be very excited about! For more information, contact Teachers On Call at 800-713-4439 , and visit them online at www.teachersoncall.com

post_text:
The Willmar Police Department has started a new community project to aid first responders in dealing with people with special needs and those that may have difficulty communicating.

Anyone using any of these stickers may sign up for the Vitals™ App free of charge. Having these stickers and the Vitals™ App will help first responders know exactly how to help, understand and provide the best kind care for you or a loved one!

Decals are available that can be placed at homes, apartments or vehicles for individuals with special needs like Autism, Alzheimer's / Dementia, deaf / hard of hearing, diabetes, epilepsy, and anxiety.
shared_text:
Willmar Police Department
March 7, 2019 at 5:20 PM ·

The Willmar Police Explorers have started a new community project to aid first responders in dealing with people with special needs and those that may have difficulty communicating.

Decals are available that can be placed at homes, apartments or vehicles for individuals with special needs like Autism, Alzheimer's / Dementia, deaf / hard of hearing, diabetes or if the occupant has medical information where the Vitals App can be utilized by responding personnel.

Thanks to the Willmar Police Explorers for working on this project! Decals are available, free of charge, at the law enforcement center & from Explorers. We will also bring them to community events.

A group photo of the Willmar Police Explorers is shown at their last training. If you know of someone between 14-20 that's interested in learning about law enforcement careers, the Explorers is a great place to start!

Food and Nutrition Services Department is looking for Food Service Assistants for the fall of 2016.

Duties include: Perform a variety of duties such as preparing, dishing and serving food items, working in the dishroom and/or pots and pans area; and assisting with kitchen clean up.

These positions require a high school diploma or equivalent and will work approximately 3 ½ hours from mid-morning to early afternoon!

Do you have what it takes? Contact the Food and Nutrition Services Director, Annette Derouin at 1-320-231-8474 to learn more or apply online at www.willmar.k12.mn.us

Duties include facilitating small groups of students in reading or math to assist in their learning. The content is kindergarten through fifth grade and requires basic skill. Training will be provided and ongoing.

post_text:
Muna '16 was one of thirty students from across the nation to serve as a Page in the U.S. Senate in the summer of 2015. She was the first Somali-American Page in the history of the U.S. Senate as well!

After building many relationships during her time as a Page, she befriended Senator Al Franken as well! Senator Franken's staff recently contacted the Willmar Senior High School to ask about attending this year's graduation ceremony to celebrate Muna along with the rest of the class of 2016. Senator Franken introduced Muna and congratulated each member of the class of 2016 as well!

post_text:
ALC students had a special visitor last week - Author Patrick Jones!

A former librarian for teens, Patrick Jones now concentrates on writing fiction for teens, particularly teens who don't like reading. Before teen fiction, Jones wrote about teens and books in over 100 articles/chapters/essays, and in nine books. His most recent, and last, professional publication is "Connecting with Reluctant Readers" (Neal-Schuman, 2006).

In 2006, Jones won lifetime achievement awards from both the Catholic Library Association and the American Library Association. Jones was a frequent speaker at library conferences visiting all fifty states, as well as in Canada, Singapore, Germany, Australia, and New Zealand!

Jones grew up in Flint, Michigan but now resides in Minneapolis.

420 of the 1,275 votes cast in Monday's Willmar School Board special election were for Justin Bos. Justin will now succeed former board member Mike Carlson who resigned when he and his family moved out of the district. Justin will fill out Carlson’s unexpired term until the end of 2016.

post_text: WPS staff members are spending this week at the Orange Frog Workshop where they will receive training that brings the happiness advantage to life at work. A team from ITLN is leading the course with content based on Shawn Anchor's research in positive psychology. Anchor has done work at Harvard and discovered that positive attitudes are contagious and proves that success follows happiness.

post_text:
Breakfast of Champions took place last week at the Middle School!

Breakfast of Champions is a program that allows any staff member to pick a student that they feel stands out above the rest. There are no requirements for who is picked other than they can receive this honor just one time. A letter is sent home by Principal, Mr. Miley, inviting the parents to come to the celebration breakfast. The staff member calls the student up to the front and gives a one-minute description of why that student was nominated. The student is then given a t-shirt and a medal to symbolize recognition!

One more Breakfast of Champions is scheduled for May 18! Approximately 35 students are honored each year at WMS! #GoCardinals

post_text:
Brady and Cory of WHS have been named one of four regional winners in the annual Toyota TeenDrive365 Video Challenge and have won $1,000!

Now in it's fifth year, the Toyota and Discovery Education Challenge invites teens across the country to create public service videos to inspire their friends and peers to drive safely! To learn more about the resources offered through TeenDrive365: In School, visit www.teendrive365inschool.com. #WaytoGoCardinals

post_text:
We have STATE CHAMPIONS to congratulate! The Willmar FFA Ag Mechanics team placed first at the contest held at the Minnesota State Fair Grounds in conjunction with the Minnesota State FFA Convention held April 24-26.

The team was also crowned champions at the University of Minnesota - Crookston contest, Ridgewater College Skills Fest contest, Region 5 FFA contest, and the South Central Technical College contest held in Mankato!

#GoCardinals
